id: pm-7u9j
title: Add narrow pm_append MCP tool for agent log-seeding without pm_run passthrough
description: "pm_run action='append' routes through the generic catch-all handler with no top-level schema. Agents that want to seed a body or log entry into an existing item must pass all options inside `options: {}`. A narrow pm_append tool would surface `id` and `options` at the top level (like pm_comments, pm_notes), participate in the unexpected-key warning system (pm-qxwu), and be self-documenting in tools/list. Append is a frequent agent operation — closing a task often involves adding evidence before close."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 3
tags[3]: agent-ux,"area:mcp",dx
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:03:51.603Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-10T15:13:44.108Z"
assignee: mcp-tools-agent
author: audit-platform-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- Narrow `pm_append` MCP tool exists, mapping to `pm append`\n- Registered in PM_TOOL_ACTIONS + tool schema/parameter contracts\n- Compact-by-default output; covered by MCP tool-list test\n- docs/AGENT_GUIDE MCP tool table updated"
parent: pm-5k4v
risk: low
confidence: high
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-10T15:13:43.022Z",mcp-tools-agent,"Implemented narrow pm_append MCP tool mapping to pm append: id (required) + body + fullChangedFields + options top-level, like pm_comments/pm_notes. body is hoisted into options in optionsWithAuthor (action=append) so runAppend receives it; options.body still wins on conflict. Output is compact by default via the existing withMutationCompaction path (changed_field_count instead of changed_fields). Participates in the unexpected-key warning system; advertised in server instructions (and removed append from the pm_run-only action enumeration there). Verified end-to-end in the handshake spec: append via top-level body, no warnings, changed_field_count=1, body visible via pm_get depth=full."
